<title>USA: Worldtex Q4 shr rises to $0.17.</title>
<headline>Worldtex Q4 shr rises to $0.17.</headline>
<dateline>HICKORY, N.C. 1997-03-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>(In thousands, except per share data)</p>
<p>					 Year Ended	Quarter Ended</p>
<p>					 December 31	December 31</p>
<p>				     1996	1995    1996     1995</p>
<p> Net Sales		    $207,829 $ 187,981 $52,640  $45,172</p>
<p> Net Income		     10,946    5,252*   2,539     359*</p>
<p>Income per common and</p>
<p>  common equivalent shares     .75	.36*     .17     .02*</p>
<p>Average number of common</p>
<p>and common equivalent</p>
<p>  shares			  14,669    14,567  14,860   14,591</p>
<p>* The results for the 1995 quarter include a restructuring charge of $1,088 or eight cents a share.  The results for the full year in 1995 include an additional one-time charge of $889 or six cents a share made in the third quarter to increase the liability for deferred income taxes caused by an increase in the French income tax rate.</p>
<p>Full company name is  Worldtex Inc.</p>
<p>--((New York Newsdesk 212 859-1610))</p>
